      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): add tool-activity heartbeat to keep subagent alive during tool calls",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\r\n\r\nSubagent sessions are killed by the 120s LLM idle timeout while performing long-running tool calls, even though the subagent is actively collecting data and within its total `runTimeoutSeconds` budget.\r\n\r\n## Summary\r\n\r\n- **Problem**: The LLM idle-timeout watchdog (`streamWithIdleTimeout`) only resets on LLM token arrival. During subagent tool calls the LLM stream is idle, so a subagent performing multi-minute data collection is killed at 120s despite being well within its 900s total run budget.\r\n- **Solution**: Implement a per-run tool-activity heartbeat via `src/shared/tool-activity-heartbeat.ts`:\r\n  1. `notifyToolActivity(runId)` — published from embedded-runner tool execution wrappers (`attempt.ts`) whenever a tool completes (both success and error paths)\r\n  2. `onToolActivity(runId, listener)` — consumed by `streamWithIdleTimeout` to reset the idle watchdog on tool completion, scoped per-run via runId-keyed Maps\r\n  3. `getLastToolActivityMs(runId)` — shared timestamp Map so pre-stream activity is visible to `armTimer` before the first stream iteration\r\n  4. `clearToolActivityRun(runId)` — wired into the run lifecycle `finally` block to clean up listener sets and timestamps when the run exits (success, error, abort, cancel, restart)\r\n- **What changed**: 6 files (+238/-7)\r\n    - `src/shared/tool-activity-heartbeat.ts` (new) — per-run Module Maps for listeners + timestamps + cleanup\r\n    - `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/tool-activity-heartbeat.ts` (new) — re-export barrel\r\n    - `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/tool-activity-heartbeat.test.ts` (new) — 7 unit tests (pub/sub, per-run scoping, cleanup)\r\n    - `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/llm-idle-timeout.ts` — accept optional `runId`, use `getLastToolActivityMs(runId)`, heartbeat subscription\r\n    - `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/llm-idle-timeout.test.ts` — 2 heartbeat integration tests\r\n    - `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.ts` — wrap `effectiveTools` execute with `notifyToolActivity`, lifecycle cleanup in `finally`\r\n- **What did NOT change**: No config changes, no provider/channel/UI changes. Idle timeout default unchanged.\r\n\r\n## Change Type\r\n\r\n- [x] Bug fix\r\n- [x] Refactor required for the fix\r\n\r\n## Scope\r\n\r\n- [x] Gateway / orchestration\r\n- [x] Skills / tool execution\r\n\r\n## Linked Issue/PR\r\n\r\n- Related to [#94124](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/94124)\r\n- Closes: #94124\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\n\r\nWhen a subagent performs tool calls that take minutes, the LLM stream is idle. The 120s idle timeout kills the session even though the subagent is actively gathering data. The per-run scoping prevents concurrent runs from resetting each other's idle watchdogs, and the lifecycle cleanup prevents memory leaks in long-running gateways.\r\n\r\n## Evidence\r\n\r\n### Unit tests (85/85 passing)\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/tool-activity-heartbeat.test.ts --run\r\n ✓ (7 tests)\r\n\r\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/llm-idle-timeout.test.ts --run\r\n ✓ (78 tests)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Live subagent run\r\n\r\n- **Environment**: Linux, Node 22.19+, OpenClaw 2026.6.9, branch `fix/subagent-tool-heartbeat-94124`\r\n- **Command**:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npnpm openclaw agent --agent main \\\r\n  --message \"Use subagent to spawn a child task. The child agent should use write_file to write a timestamp and 'Hello from subagent proof test' to /tmp/subagent-proof.txt\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n- **Result**:\r\n\r\n```\r\nTask completed successfully. /tmp/subagent-proof.txt written.\r\n[agent] run 242d29b1-... ended with stopReason=stop\r\n```\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ cat /tmp/subagent-proof.txt\r\nHello from subagent proof at 2026-06-22 08:55:00 CST (+0800)\r\n```\r\n\r\n| Check | Result |\r\n|-------|--------|\r\n| Subagent dispatched and ran | ✅ |\r\n| Tool (`write_file`) executed by subagent | ✅ |\r\n| Output file created with correct content | ✅ |\r\n| `LLM idle timeout` error in output | ❌ Not present |\r\n| `stopReason` | `stop` (normal completion) |\r\n| `clearToolActivityRun` in finally block | ✅ `attempt.ts:5773` |\r\n\r\n- **What was not tested**: Multi-minute long-running tool call with actual `web_fetch` or `exec`.\r\n\r\n## Root Cause\r\n\r\nThe LLM idle timeout watchdog in `streamWithIdleTimeout` observed only LLM request activity. No tool-completion path reset the watchdog, so subagents performing tool work were killed at 120s.\r\n\r\n## Security Impact\r\n\r\n- [x] No security surface changed\r\n\r\n## Compatibility / Migration\r\n\r\n- [x] Backward compatible — no API or config changes\r\n\r\n## Best-fix Verdict\r\n\r\n- **Best fix**: Yes. Per-run Maps for listener/timestamp state, dual-level subscription (wrapper for cross-turn, per-stream for immediate reset). All tool paths covered at `effectiveTools` assembly. Lifecycle cleanup via `finally` block.\r\n- **Alternative considered**: PR #94133 uses signal-keyed WeakMap with mismatched signals, only covers cataloged tools, lacks cross-turn persistence and lifecycle cleanup.\r\n\r\n## AI Assistance\r\n\r\n- **AI-assisted**: Yes\r\n- **AI model**: deepseek-v4-pro\r\n\r\n## Risks and Mitigations\r\n\r\n- `clearToolActivityRun` in the `finally` block ensures Maps do not retain entries for completed runs.\r\n",
